item.title: Big Ls Brother Talks New Return of The Devils Son LP, Roc-A-Fella Recruitment & Mase
item.description: (photo credit: Destiny Mata) It’s been more than a decade since the hip-hop world lost Lamont “Big L” Coleman to street violence. Born and raised in Harlem, L’s influence on the Uptown rap scene can still be felt today, as he schooled MCs like Mase and Cam’Ron and on the art of rhyme. With his second posthumous album, Return of the Devil’s Son, scheduled for release a Nov. 23 release, VIBE located Big L’s oldest brother Donald Phinazee—who is executive producing the project—to shed some light on the new album, the real Big L, his relationship with fellow Children of the Corn members, and how close L really was to signing with Jay-Z.

item.title: Burke Dales Children: Did Burke Dales Have Kids?
item.description: It is unclear if Burke Dales had children or not. There is no information about his children on the Internet as he liked to keep his personal life away from the limelight. Dales’s professional journey commenced when he was signed by the Pittsburgh Steelers as an undrafted free agent in 2002. His time at the Steelers’ training camp displayed not only his punting prowess but also his attempt to break into the league as a kick-off specialist.

item.title: RHONJ: The Truth About Dina And Tommy Manzo's Relationship Drama
item.description: Dina Manzo starred on the hit Bravo reality show "The Real Housewives of New Jersey" for four seasons, however, the star has officially left Jersey for California and doesn't appear to be returning anytime soon. Dina starred alongside her sister, Caroline Manzo, however, the two sisters are no longer speaking to one another after years of betrayal and backstabbing. During her time on the show, Dina was married to Tommy Manzo, who just so happened to be the brother to Caroline's husband, Albert Manzo.

item.description: Why is standup comedian Margaret Cho so popular on social media? Many stars like her take to apps like Twitter and Instagram and see a modest degree of success here and there, and others go viral by just existing. item.description: Actress Brie Larson is no stranger to online scrutiny. The award-winning 30-year old California native took on the role of Carol Danvers for the 2019 Captain Marvel film, but it earned a mix of praises and criticism. Not even her Best Actress award for the 2015 drama/thriller film Room and all the other accolades she has earned since starting her acting career in the 90s, have shielded her from the critics saying that Marvel has to find another actress to play the coveted role of Captain Marvel.

item.title: Anne Hathaway Wears Daring Corset Dress at The Idea of You Premiere
item.description: Corsets have been all the rage this year, and Anne Hathaway found a way to keep the trend fresh and fun at the New York City premiere of her new film, The Idea of You. Hathaway, 41, graced the Monday, April 29, red carpet in a crimson Versace gown. The look featured a bandeau bodice with cutouts at the bust. The openings were intricately connected to waist-cinching paneling, resembling a deconstructed corset.

item.title: Bobby Wood (Politician) Obituary, Funeral
item.description: Bobby G. Wood was an American politician. Wood was born on September 21, 1935 and died on January 12, 2023. He was 87 years. Wood was born in Fyffe, Alabama. He lived in Harrison, Tennessee, with his wife and family, and was involved with the insurance business and the Chattanooga Glass Company. In politics, Wood served in the Tennessee House of Representatives from 1976 to 2004 and was a Republican. State Senator Bo Watson paid tribute to Wood, singling him out for his ability to work with Democrats.
